cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper describes an architecture for robots to represent and reason with uncertainty and domain knowledge, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of logical reasoning and probabilistic algorithms, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and probabilistic graphical models (cs.LO). The architecture also involves a controller component, which is related to control systems (cs.SY), and a logician component, which uses declarative programming (cs.PL). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.RO and cs.AI, followed by cs.LO, cs.SY, and cs.PL.
